//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_depot_inscribe}

NOTE: This operation mirrors upstream tool images (gcloud, docker, alpine, syft, binfmt, skopeo) into a datestamped GAR namespace within the
{rbtgi_depot}.
The resulting reliquary is referenced by vessel regimes via `RBRV_RELIQUARY` and consumed at conjure time as the toolchain source.

The
{rbtr_director}
inscribes a reliquary:

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_director}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_director_authenticate}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DIRECTOR_TOKEN»` for subsequent API calls

//axhos_step
. *Derive Reliquary Datestamp*:
.. {rbbc_store}
`«RELIQUARY»` as `r` + `YYMMDDHHMMSS` from current time
.. Example: `r260415120000`

//axhos_step
. *Submit Inscribe Cloud Build*:
.. Construct Build resource JSON with:
... step image: `gcr.io/cloud-builders/docker` (Google-hosted, always pullable)
... step script: `rbgji01-inscribe-mirror.sh` (docker pull/tag/push per tool image)
... substitutions: `_RBGN_GAR_HOST`, `_RBGN_GAR_PATH`, `_RBGN_RELIQUARIES_ROOT`, `_RBGN_RELIQUARY`
... resulting tool image path shape: `${_RBGN_GAR_HOST}/${_RBGN_GAR_PATH}/{gar_reliquaries_namespace}/${_RBGN_RELIQUARY}/<tool>:${_RBGN_RELIQUARY}` (both path segment and tag are the reliquary datestamp, per the categorical layout)
... serviceAccount:
{rbtr_mason}
... pool: tethered (upstream pull requires public egress)
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»` as `${RBRD_CLOUD_PREFIX}d-${RBRD_DEPOT_MONIKER}` (resolved by `RBDC_DEPOT_PROJECT_ID`)
.. {rbbc_submit}
link:https://cloud.google.com/build/docs/api/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.builds/create[builds.create] with:
... project:
`«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»`
... location:
{rbrd_gcp_region}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«BUILD_ID»` from response `.metadata.build.id`
.. {rbbc_show}
build dispatched with `«BUILD_ID»`
.. {rbbc_show}
Cloud Console URL for build monitoring

//axhos_step
. *Wait for Build Completion*:
.. {rbbc_poll}
link:https://cloud.google.com/build/docs/api/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.builds/get[cloudbuild.builds.get] for `«BUILD_ID»`
.. Poll at 5-second intervals for up to 120 attempts (~10 minutes)
.. {rbbc_require}
final status is `SUCCESS`

//axhoot_typed_output
{rbf_fact_reliquary}
. *Write Fact File*:
.. {rbbc_store}
{rbf_fact_reliquary}
with value `«RELIQUARY»`

//axhoc_completion
Successful execution mirrors all tool images into the reliquary namespace.
Set `RBRV_RELIQUARY=«RELIQUARY»` in vessel {rbrv_regime} files to use this reliquary for subsequent conjure operations.

//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_director_roster}

NOTE: This operation rosters
{rbtr_director}
{giam_service_account_s}
in the
{rbtgi_depot_project}
via per-SA fact-file emission.
Read-only observation: lists all SAs, filters to director-prefixed emails, and emits one fact per discovered SA via
{buf_write_fact_multi}
against the `RBCC_fact_ext_roster_director` extension constant.
Fact value is the full SA email; `file_root` is the bare identity extracted from the email.

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_governor}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_governor_authenticate}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«GOVERNOR_TOKEN»` from the resulting access token

//axhos_step
. *List service accounts*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts/list[iam.projects.serviceAccounts.list] with:
... method: `GET`
... endpoint: `https://iam.googleapis.com/v1/projects/{rbtgi_depot_project}/serviceAccounts`
... header: `Authorization: Bearer «GOVERNOR_TOKEN»`
.. {rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 response
.. {rbbc_store}
`«ACCOUNTS»` from response `.accounts[]` array

//axhos_step
. *Filter to director service accounts*:
.. From `«ACCOUNTS»`, read the `.email` field of each entry and test whether it matches `^${RBCC_account_director}-(.+)@${RBGD_SA_EMAIL_FULL}$`
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DIRECTOR_EMAILS»` — the matching emails; per-role observation per BBAAQ contract

//axhos_step
. *Emit Fact Per Discovered {rbtr_director}*:
.. For each `«SA_EMAIL»` in `«DIRECTOR_EMAILS»`:
... {rbbc_store}
`«IDENTITY»` from the regex capture group — the portion of `«SA_EMAIL»` between `${RBCC_account_director}-` and `@${RBGD_SA_EMAIL_FULL}`
... {rbbc_call}
{buf_write_fact_multi}
with three positional arguments:
.... `<file_root>`: `«IDENTITY»` (bare identity — the basename root for the emitted fact file)
.... `<ext>`: `RBCC_fact_ext_roster_director` (resolves at source time to `roster-director`)
.... `<value>`: `«SA_EMAIL»` (the full service account email address)

//axhos_step
. *Report count*:
.. {rbbc_show}
total count of emitted director fact files

//axhoc_completion
Successful execution rosters {rbtr_director} service accounts via per-SA fact emission — one `roster-director` fact file per discovered identity, each containing the full SA email as its value.
The operation is read-only; no service accounts are created or modified.

//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_ark_abjure}

NOTE: This operation formally renounces an
{rbtga_ark}
from
{rbtgi_repository}
by enumerating and deleting every package beneath the ark's
hallmark subtree via the GAR REST API implemented by
{gar_service}.

An
{rbtga_ark}
is the coherent unit of a Recipe Bottle build: a set of packages rooted at
`{gar_hallmarks_namespace}/«HALLMARK»/` and distinguished by basename.
The
{rbtga_ark_image}
(basename `image`) contains the container image itself.
The
{rbtga_ark_about}
(basename `about`) contains SBOM and build metadata.
The
{rbtga_ark_vouch}
(basename `vouch`) contains verification results.
The
{rbtga_ark_pouch}
(basename `pouch`) contains the build context (conjure/bind only, absent for graft).
A fifth basename, `diags`, is present for conjure arks only (build-time diagnostics forwarded to the about pipeline).
For conjure vessels, a single `attest` package holds per-platform tags (`attest:«HALLMARK»-«ARCH»`).
Abjuring an ark deletes every package discovered beneath the hallmark subtree as a single logical operation.

The
{rbtr_director}
abjures an ark:

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{rbtga_ark}
. *Validate Input Parameters*:
.. {rbbc_require}
`«INPUT_VESSEL»` provided as first argument (retained for AAK signature compatibility; not used to construct the subtree path, drops in AAL)
.. {rbbc_require}
`«INPUT_HALLMARK»` provided as second argument
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if hallmark missing: "Hallmark parameter required"

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{rbtga_hallmark}
. *Validate Hallmark Format*:
.. {rbbc_require}
`«INPUT_HALLMARK»` matches pattern `[cbg]\d{12}-r\d{12}` (mode prefix + dual timestamp)
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if malformed: "Hallmark format invalid"

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_director}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_director_authenticate}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DIRECTOR_TOKEN»` for subsequent API calls

//axhos_step
. *Construct Hallmark Subtree*:
.. {rbbc_store}
`«SUBTREE»` as `«HALLMARKS_ROOT»/«INPUT_HALLMARK»/` where `«HALLMARKS_ROOT»` derives from `RBGL_HALLMARKS_ROOT` (kindled to `{gar_hallmarks_namespace}`)
.. {rbbc_store}
`«REPO_BASE»` as the GAR REST API repository base (`projects/«PROJECT»/locations/«REGION»/repositories/«REPOSITORY»`)

//axhos_step
. *Enumerate Packages Under Subtree*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/artifact-registry/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.repositories.packages/list[GAR REST API: packages.list] with:
... method: `GET`
... endpoint: `«REPO_BASE»/packages?pageSize=1000`
... header: `Authorization: Bearer «DIRECTOR_TOKEN»`
.. {rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 response
.. Extract `.packages[].name` from the response, strip the resource prefix, and URL-decode `%2F` back to `/`
.. {rbbc_store}
`«ARK_PACKAGES»` as the list of decoded package names whose prefix equals `«SUBTREE»`
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if `«ARK_PACKAGES»` is empty: "No packages found under «SUBTREE» — hallmark not present in registry"

//axhos_step
. *Confirm Abjuration*:
.. {rbbc_show}
"Will abjure «COUNT» packages under «SUBTREE»:" followed by each entry in `«ARK_PACKAGES»`
.. {rbbc_require}
user types `yes` to confirm
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if not confirmed: "prompt not confirmed."

//axhos_step
. *Delete Each Enumerated Package*:
.. For each `«PACKAGE»` in `«ARK_PACKAGES»`:
... {rbbc_store}
`«ENCODED»` as `«PACKAGE»` with `/` replaced by `%2F`
... {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/artifact-registry/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.repositories.packages/delete[GAR REST API: packages.delete] with:
.... method: `DELETE`
.... endpoint: `«REPO_BASE»/packages/«ENCODED»`
.... header: `Authorization: Bearer «DIRECTOR_TOKEN»`
... {rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 response (deletion returns a long-running operation; the 200 is treated as accepted)
... {rbbc_fatal}
if delete fails: "Failed to delete package «PACKAGE» (HTTP «STATUS_CODE»)"

//axhoot_typed_output
{rbtga_ark}
. *Display Results*:
.. {rbbc_show}
"Hallmark abjured: «INPUT_HALLMARK» («COUNT» packages)"
.. For each deleted package:
... {rbbc_show}
`  - «PACKAGE» deleted`

//axhoc_completion
Procedure completes successfully when every package discovered beneath the hallmark subtree has been deleted from the registry and the abjuration confirmation is displayed.
The ark is now formally renounced and no longer part of the repository corpus.
Because enumeration drives the delete set, there is no separate existence check and no orphan-detection branch: whatever lives in the subtree is removed, and an empty subtree is itself the "not present" signal.
Deleting a package removes all of its tags in one call — per-basename HEAD/DELETE dances are no longer required.

//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_ark_enshrine}

NOTE: This operation enshrines upstream base images into
{gar_service}
as content-addressed, human-readable anchors.
The
{rbtr_director}
submits a Cloud Build job that copies each declared
{rbrv_image_origin}
from its upstream registry to GAR using
the reliquary skopeo image
(`skopeo copy --all`), preserving the manifest list and all per-platform manifests for multi-platform images.
The locator results are returned via `buildStepOutputs` and
{rbrv_image_anchor}
is then written back to the vessel regime locally as a
{rbst_locator}.

NOTE: This operation is a pure mirror.
Every call inspects current upstream for each declared
{rbrv_image_origin}
, computes the content-addressed locator from the live manifest digest, copies the image into
{gar_service}
, and writes the resulting
{rbst_locator}
into the vessel's
{rbrv_image_anchor}
— overwriting whatever was previously committed there.
The
{rbrv_image_anchor}
is a derived artifact of this operation, not an operator-set pin.
Re-runs are idempotent with respect to upstream state, not with respect to the file's prior contents — when upstream rotates, the next call writes a different locator and that is the operation surfacing the change, not a fault.

NOTE: Vessels whose
{rbrv_image_anchor}
is written by an upstream procedure as a hallmark-pin (e.g., the airgap-bottle pointing at the just-ordained forge image via `{gar_hallmarks_namespace}/«HALLMARK»/«BASENAME»:«HALLMARK»`) do not invoke this operation.
The orchestrating procedure (handbook step or onboarding-sequence fixture) writes the locator directly;
{rbtgo_ark_conjure}
resolves it at build time.
The hallmark's existence in
{gar_service}
is established by the producer's
{rbtgo_ark_ordain}
success, not by a separate validation step here.

NOTE: Enshrine is a pre-build preparation step.
It must be run before
{rbtgo_ark_conjure}
when anchored base images are desired.
Conjure works without anchors (passing ORIGIN through), but anchored images provide reproducibility and air-gap readiness.

NOTE: Enshrine runs on Cloud Build, not the Director's workstation.
No local skopeo installation is required.
The GCB step uses Mason SA ambient credentials via the metadata server for GAR writes.

NOTE: The enshrine Cloud Build job carries the {rbsk_in_pool_preflight} as its step 0, ahead of the skopeo copy. Enshrine passes empty locator substitutions — enshrine's purpose is to create anchors, so pre-validating them would be circular.

The enshrine operation:

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{rbrv_sigil}
. *Validate Input Parameters*:
.. {rbbc_require}
vessel provided as first argument
.. {rbbc_require}
vessel declares at least one upstream base-image slot — that is, at least one of slots 1-3 has
{rbrv_image_origin}
populated.
{rbrv_image_anchor}
is computed by this operation; an ANCHOR-only slot is not a valid input shape
.. {rbbc_require}
vessel mode is `conjure` (`RBRV_VESSEL_MODE`)
.. {rbbc_require}
reliquary tool images exist in GAR (HEAD check on `docker:latest` canary)

//axhos_step
. *Submit Enshrine Cloud Build Job*:
.. Compose `builds.create` JSON with:
... Single step using
the reliquary skopeo image
as the builder image (script: `rbgje01-enshrine-copy.sh`)
... `_RBGE_*` substitutions: `_RBGE_GAR_HOST`, `_RBGE_GAR_PATH`, `_RBGE_IMAGE_n_ORIGIN` (n = 1, 2, 3; empty for unused slots). Base images are stored in the shared `{gar_enshrines_namespace}/` namespace, with each anchor as a peer package (`{gar_enshrines_namespace}/«ANCHOR»:«ANCHOR»`), not per-vessel.
... Mason SA, private pool, timeout
.. Submit via `builds.create` and wait for completion
.. The GCB step, for each non-empty ORIGIN slot:
... Fetches the raw upstream manifest (`skopeo inspect --raw`) and computes its sha256 digest (`sha256sum` of the raw manifest bytes)
... {rbbc_store}
`<<DIGEST>>` -- the sha256 digest of the upstream manifest (manifest list digest for multi-platform images, single manifest digest for single-platform images)
... Constructs anchor: sanitize full origin string (`:` `/` replaced with `-`), append first 10 hex chars of sha256 digest
... Example: `python:3.11-slim` with `sha256:abc123def4...` yields anchor `python-3.11-slim-abc123def4`
... Composes the
{rbst_locator}
as `{gar_enshrines_namespace}/«ANCHOR»:«ANCHOR»` (e.g., `{gar_enshrines_namespace}/python-3.11-slim-abc123def4:python-3.11-slim-abc123def4`)
... Copies upstream image into the shared `{gar_enshrines_namespace}/` namespace in GAR as a peer package at `{gar_enshrines_namespace}/«ANCHOR»:«ANCHOR»` using `skopeo copy --all`, transferring the manifest list and all per-platform manifests atomically. Each anchor is its own package under the namespace — the path segment carries the anchor identity, and the tag redundantly restates it so divergence is a visible bug. The anchor is vessel-independent — multiple vessels sharing the same base image origin share one enshrined package.
... {rbbc_require}
copy succeeds -- the locator now resolves to a permanent, content-addressed reference in
{gar_service}
containing all upstream platforms
... Single-platform upstream images are handled identically -- `skopeo copy --all` is a no-op on the platform dimension when only one platform exists
.. Writes JSON locator results to `/builder/outputs/output` (returned as `buildStepOutputs`); each slot's `anchor` field carries the full locator string

//axhos_step
. *Extract Locators and Write Regime*:
.. Read `buildStepOutputs[0]` from the completed build result (base64-decoded JSON)
.. For each slot present in the result:
... Write locator string to `RBRV_IMAGE_n_ANCHOR` in the vessel's {rbrv_regime} file, overwriting any prior value

//axhoot_typed_output
{rbrv_image_anchor}
Per-slot locator string written to the vessel regime.

//axhoc_completion
Successful execution produces anchored base image references in
{gar_service}
(with all upstream platforms preserved) and updates the vessel regime with
{rbrv_image_anchor}
values.
The vessel is now ready for reproducible
{rbtgo_ark_conjure}
builds using GAR-mirrored base images.
Multi-platform conjure vessels pull the correct platform from the anchored manifest list automatically.
Re-running enshrine with the same
{rbrv_image_origin}
but a different upstream digest produces a new locator (upstream image was updated).
Re-running with the same digest is idempotent.

{rbtgi_depot_project}
via per-SA fact-file emission
({rbtgog_governor}).

include::RBSRL-retriever_roster.adoc[]

== {rbtr_director} Operations

[[rbtgo_trigger_build]]
//axvo_method axd_transient axd_grouped
=== {rbtgo_trigger_build}

ELIMINATED: Trigger dispatch replaced by direct `builds.create` API submission.
Build context delivered via {rbtga_ark_pouch} (FROM SCRATCH OCI image in GAR).
Hallmark minted on the host before submission, passed to Cloud Build via `_RBGY_HALLMARK` substitution variable.

// include::RBSTB-trigger_build.adoc[]

NOTE: For multi-platform build authentication challenges and research findings, see link:RBWMBX-BuildxMultiPlatformAuth.adoc[RBWMBX: Buildx Multi-Platform Authentication Memo].

[[rbtgo_depot_inscribe]]
//axvo_method axd_transient axd_grouped
=== {rbtgo_depot_inscribe}

Inscribes a reliquary into the
{rbtgi_depot}:
mirrors upstream tool images into a datestamped GAR namespace
({rbtgog_depot}).

include::RBSDI-depot_inscribe.adoc[]

[[rbtgo_director_yoke]]
//axvo_method axd_transient axd_grouped
=== {rbtgo_director_yoke}

Yokes a reliquary stamp across every vessel's
{rbrv_regime}:
validates the stamp once against GAR, then rewrites `RBRV_RELIQUARY` in every {rbrv_regime} file under `${RBRR_VESSEL_DIR}`
({rbtgog_depot}).

include::RBSDY-director_yoke.adoc[]

[[rbtgo_image_delete]]
//axvo_method axd_transient axd_grouped
=== {rbtgo_image_delete}

Jettisons a single
{rbtgi_image}
artifact by
{rbst_locator}
({rbtgog_image}).
Locator-generic across hallmark members, reliquary tool images, and enshrinement images.

include::RBSIJ-image_jettison.adoc[]

[[rbtgo_image_retrieve]]
//axvo_method axd_transient axd_grouped
=== {rbtgo_image_retrieve}

Wrests a single
{rbtgi_image}
artifact by
{rbst_locator}
({rbtgog_image}).
Locator-generic across hallmark members, reliquary tool images, and enshrinement images.
{rbtr_director}-tier — peer to {rbtgo_image_delete}, distinct from {rbtgo_ark_summon}.

include::RBSIW-image_wrest.adoc[]

