//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_lode_banish}

NOTE: This operation banishes a whole
{rbtga_lode}
from
{gar_service}
via a single GAR `packages delete` on the touchmark package — the atomic whole-Lode delete.
Kind-agnostic; the fetched-side parallel of made-side
{rbtgo_ark_abjure}.

NOTE: A
{rbtga_lode}
is exactly one GAR package, so `packages delete` removes the package and all its member versions and tags in one call.
("Atomic" = single operation, not transactional rollback.)
Banishment is whole-Lode; single-member cleanup — the fix-a-bad-member case — is a member/tag-grain operation in the image family ({rbtgo_image_delete}), not here.

The
{rbtr_director}
banishes a Lode:

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{rbtga_touchmark}
. *Validate Input Parameters*:
.. {rbbc_require}
`«TOUCHMARK»` provided as the operation folio
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if missing: "Touchmark parameter required"

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_director}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_director_authenticate}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DIRECTOR_TOKEN»` for subsequent API calls

//axhos_step
. *Verify Lode Present*:
.. {rbbc_call}
GAR REST `tags.list` (pageSize 1) for the package `{gar_lodes_namespace}/«TOUCHMARK»`
.. {rbbc_require}
at least one tag present
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if none: "No Lode found at «PACKAGE» — nothing to banish"

//axhos_step
. *Confirm Banishment*:
.. {rbbc_show}
"Will banish the whole Lode «PACKAGE» (single packages delete)"
.. {rbbc_require}
user types `yes` to confirm
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if not confirmed: "prompt not confirmed."

//axhos_step
. *Delete Lode Package*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/artifact-registry/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.repositories.packages/delete[GAR REST API: packages.delete] for `{gar_lodes_namespace}/«TOUCHMARK»`
.. {rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 response (deletion returns a long-running operation; the 200 is treated as accepted)

//axhoot_typed_output
{rbtga_lode}
. *Display Result*:
.. {rbbc_show}
"Lode banished: «TOUCHMARK»"

//axhoc_completion
Procedure completes when the touchmark package — the whole
{rbtga_lode}
with every member version and tag — has been removed from
{gar_service}
in one `packages delete`.
+
A presence probe drives the confirmation, so an absent Lode is reported as a clean "nothing to banish" rather than a delete error.
Because one Lode is one package, there is no per-member dance and no orphan-detection branch — the single delete is the whole operation.
If GAR ever refuses a single-call delete of a mixed-artifact package, the fallback is a pool-run delete loop over the package's tags, effectively atomic for these purposes.

